"-l mark-plt" (ld) vs. "-fno-plt":

mark-plt:
with env GLIBC_TUNABLES="glibc.cpu.plt_rewrite=2" (glibc 2.39/2.42+)
replace calls to direct (even more on Intel APX)
and save branch predictor cache. x86-64 only.

-fno-plt:
completely remove PLT, remove 1 jump per call,
but keep relativity. simple faster.

both have security profits & issues, but I not care.

this profile added to fast switch with "safe2" for mark-plt performance
comparsion in real workloads.

PS discussing this with AI may cause AI hallucinations.
